name: Oleana
notes: Best upscale Mediterranean food in the city.
Service is always gracious and attentive and helpful without being overbearing.
Hands down, the best outdoor dining in the city is Oleana's secret garden.

name: Lonestar Taco Bar
notes: Definitely go here for delicious food and bomb margs!
Al pastor tacos make me gooo crrAzzZZyy.
The guac was OBVIOUSLY homemade and super fresh.

name: S&S Restaurant
notes: Get an order of pickles, you wont regret it.
Delicious bakery- I always get the lemon poppy seed cookies.

name: Little Donkey
notes: The tapas were all very delicious and inspired.
Sit outside and treat yourself to an incredible cocktail!

name: Life Alive
notes: An eclectic menu with a hippie vibe.
My all time favorite food place in Boston!
